definition.value: An elevation which is relatively low.
A viscosity which relatively high.

value.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting complete growth, differentiation, or development.
A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension.
A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.
A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions.

definition.value: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to lose an entitity by natural process.
A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.
A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

value.value: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to convey electricity.

definition.value: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing granules.

value.value: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being confined or restricted to multiple locations.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's being covered by a liquid.
A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered by a liquid.
A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being covered by a liquid.
A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing acid (hydrogen ions).
A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward.

definition.value: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a consistently-sized round cross section.

value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

value.value: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.
Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

definition.value: A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.
A structural quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing hollow areas.
A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's layered configuration.
A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an empty space or cavity within.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

value.value: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being free of curves, bends, or angles.

definition.value: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in position.

value.value: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane.
A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.
A cylindrical shape that is hollow.
A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

value.value: A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.
An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.
A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer's water vapour content.

definition.value: An increase in humidity.
The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.

value.value: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

label.value: quality of interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation

value.value: A quality of a substance on which or through which electromagnetic radiation impinges or traverses with respect to radiation. This substance quality changes the quality of the incident radiation with respect to any of: intensity, direction, scatter and wavelength.

definition.value: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.
